The situation is slightly different when the responses of men and women are analyzed separately.
Thus, 28% of men are very satisfied, 39% satisfied, 17% appropriate, 6% very unsatisfied and 8% slightly unsatisfied.
As for women, 33% said they were satisfied, 24% very satisfied, 8% very unsatisfied, 14% slightly unsatisfied and 19% chose the right category.
When we look at the degree of satisfaction (positive), we will notice that men are more satisfied.
In terms of the neutral (fit) state, we see a difference of two percent.
"As well as in the very unsatisfied situation, the biggest difference being the slightly unsatisfied response where we see a difference of 6 percent," the statement said.
The study also showed that a quarter of Romanians (26%) spend an hour or less together, 18% spend between five and eight hours together, and 45% between two and four hours.
“Romans feel they need a little more adventure in their lives (24%), followed by affection (21%), money (21%), security (20%), nine (19%), sex (19%), respect 18%, confidence 17%, pleasure 17%, connection 17%, knowledge 16%, protection 14%, importance 14%, learning 12%, freedom 11%, self-control 10%.”
