The Great Migrations
Romania is not and will not be prepared for what lies ahead.
What about Europe?
I say it from the beginning, clearly and bluntly: the 7,000 refugees that Romania should and must naturalize represent, in itself, an insignificant number, but huge compared to the Romanian state’s ability to manage such a project.
